    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Professional background</h2>
    <p>Renato Bryant brings roughly 30 years of experience in corporate management and operational environments where budgeting, compliance, oversight, and decision quality matter. That background shapes Finance Tools Hub's emphasis on transparent assumptions, structured planning logic, and real-world usability.</p>
    <p>Rather than publishing calculators as isolated widgets, the site is designed to help users understand why an output changes, which assumptions matter most, and where a structured estimate should lead to deeper professional review.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How this experience informs the site</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Focus on measurable decision inputs rather than vague personal finance commentary</li>
      <li>Preference for clear formulas and disclosed assumptions</li>
      <li>Operational perspective on risk, planning, and scenario analysis</li>
      <li>Bias toward practical business and household use cases</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Role at Finance Tools Hub</h2>
    <p>Renato Bryant oversees the structure, logic direction, editorial positioning, and practical use-case focus of Finance Tools Hub. The site is intended to make common money questions easier to model, whether the user is estimating paycheck deductions, paying down debt, projecting retirement savings, or evaluating the cost of working remotely abroad.</p>

